. Hi. gmaps has `GMaps.geocode`, which returns, in a callback, an array of google.maps.GeocoderResult objects. You can read the [reference of this object specification](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/reference#GeocoderResult) or check an [example using gmaps](http://hpneo.github.com/gmaps/examples/geocoding.html).

In the callback you can fill your inputs with the first result of `geocode`. Also, you can use jQuery UI Autocomplete with external source, just like this:

``` javascript
  $(input).autocomplete({
    source: function(request, response) {
      GMaps.geocode({
        address: request.term,
        callback: function(result, status) {
          if (status == 'OK') {
            mapped_results = $.map(result, function(geocoder_result) {
              return {
                label: place.formatted_address,
                value: place.formatted_address,
                object: geocoder_result
              };
            });
          }
          else {
            mapped_results = []
          }
          response(mapped_results);
        }
      });
    },
    select: function(event, ui) {
      $(input).val(ui.item.value);

      location = ui.item.object.geometry.location;
      fill_inputs_with_location(location);
    }
  });
```
