A little function, which helped me to count correct zoom, based on geographical radius of displayed area

``` javascript
        fit_map_on_markers= function(radius){
            var zoom = (Math.floor(2 - Math.log(1.6446 * radius / Math.sqrt(2 * ($('#'+this.canvas_selector).height() * $('#'+this.canvas_selector).width()))) / Math.log (2)));
            if(zoom>18){
                zoom = 18;
            }
            map.setZoom(zoom);
        }
```
