petri:
Here's what I figured works with require.js. One has to add:
1. a module that requires the google maps library using the async plugin for requirejs
2. a shim for gmaps.js to declare it depends on the aforementioned module (that in turn requires google maps library)

The module, let's say in 'googlemapsapi.js':

``` javascript
 define(['async!http://maps.google.com/maps/api/js?v=3&sensor=false'], function() {});
```

The module does not have to do anything. Next, the require.js configuration that forces the google maps api to be loaded before gmaps.js:

``` javascript

  require.config({
    paths: {
      "googlemapsapi": "googlemapsapi",
    },
    shim: {
      gmaps: {
        deps: ["googlemapsapi"],
        exports: "GMaps"
      }
