sivabudh:
It's not just opening inspect element, if you resized the browser, Google Maps would render.. I got it to work. Here's the code that worked for me. I hope it helps somebody out there. It uses Haml, but I'm sure any programmers can figure it out.

```
%script{src: "https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=<Your API key>", type: "text/javascript"}

:javascript
  function showGoogleMaps() {

    // Put your code here

    // I made `map` a Javascript global variable
    map = new google.maps.Map(...);

    // Same as my marker (if you needed it)
    marker = new google.maps.Marker({ ... });

    marker.setMap(map);
  }

  // and here's the key that got it to work!
  google.maps.event.addDomListener(window, 'load', showGoogleMaps)
```. Seems like someone also came across the same solution:

http://stackoverflow.com/a/29572745/65313. It's not just opening inspect element, if you resized the browser, Google Maps would render.. I got it to work. Here's the code that worked for me. I hope it helps somebody out there. It uses Haml, but I'm sure any programmers can figure it out.

